



Pods:

    - Pods managers containers    


Virtual Network:

    - Gives to each pod an IP address

Service:

    - Gives permanent IP address to the Pods, solves the problem of pods having a dynamic IP address

    - Can be attached to each pod (lifecycle of a pod and service are not connected)

    - Service at the same time Service is a load bancer


Ingress:

    Request go through ingress and ingress does the forwarding to the services


ConfigMap:

    - External configuration of application

    - Pods can connect to ConfigMap and pods get the data

    - When ConfigMap is adjusted the configuration changes automatically


Secrets:

    - Same thing as ConfigMap but is used to store secret data

    - Stored in base64 format 

    - Secrets are meant to be encrypted using 3rd party tools


Volume:

    - If Pods gets restared the data of the pod is gone

    -  Volume attaches physical storage to a pod


Deployment:

    - Handles replicas of pods and scaling in application 

    - Convienient way to configure pods

    - In practice we work with deployments, not pods direcly


StatefulSets:

    - Handles pods but it is recommend to be used for databases

    - Takes care of pods (replicas, scaling)

    - Makes sure Reads/Writes databases are synchronized
